The National Examinations Council (NECO) has raised the alarm over fraudsters purportedly recruiting staff on behalf of the council, saying it  never advertised any position on any platform. A statement by the council’s head of information and public relations, Malam Abdulzeez Sani, yesterday said NECO attention has been drawn to an on-line publication purporting that the council is planning to recruit new members of staff. “The council enjoins members of the public to disregard the publication as it has no plan to recruit new staff. We also wish to state very strongly that the publication is the product of the imagination of fraudsters who are out to defraud unsuspecting members of the public,” he added. It stated that NECO under the present leadership of the acting registrar/chief executive, Abubakar Mohammed Gana, and the governing board under Dr. Abubakar Saddiq Mohammed are on the same page with the next level mantra of the present administration of President Muhammadu Buhari which epitomizes  transparency, adherence to due process, and zero tolerance for impunity, and as such NECO will not do anything contrary to the mantra. It will be recalled that NECO has been a target of job fraudster over the years, a situation applicant attributed to lack of transparency in the recruitment process.